  "prompt": "What is Brookings, Oregon like?",
  "response": "Brookings is a small coastal city located in Curry County, Oregon, near the California border. Here are some key characteristics:\n\n1. Location\n- Situated on the southern Oregon coast\n- Part of the scenic \"Oregon Coastline\"\n- Close to the Redwood National and State Parks\n\n2. Climate\n- Mild climate due to its coastal location\n- Less rainy than other parts of Oregon\n- Known for having the warmest winter temperatures in Oregon\n\n3. Demographics\n- Small population (around 6,400 residents)\n- Predominantly retiree and senior community\n- Relatively low population density\n\n4. Economy\n- Tourism is a significant economic driver\n- Fishing and logging have historically been important\n- Increasing retirement and service-based economy\n\n5. Attractions\n- Beautiful beaches\n- Proximity to state parks\n- Harbor area\n- Oregon Redwoods nearby\n- Good fishing and outdoor recreation opportunities\n\n6. Lifestyle\n- Quiet, relaxed coastal community\n- Strong outdoor and recreational culture\n- Relatively peaceful and scenic environment\n\nThe city is known for its natural beauty, mild climate, and relaxed lifestyle, making it attractive for retirees and those seeking a slower-paced coastal community.",
